I've had Filipino food before (home cooked) but never actually went to a restaurant and had the option of choosing from an entire menu. This place was GREAT!! It's BYOB so definitely make sure to bring a bottle of something if you're a drinker. The menu has a nice selection of authentic Filipino dishes (confirmed by a Filipino friend in our group) and the food is delicious and I feel reasonably priced. I'm not a huge karaoke fan, but it was entertaining to watch everyone else- dinner and a show lol. The staff is extremely attentive, friendly and the over all experience exceeded expectations (never heard of the place and was turned off when I heard they had karaoke). I will definitely be back!!
